[Adelaide, with a metropolitan population (including suburbs) of more than 1 345 777 residents, is the capital of the Australian state of South Australia, and the 5th-most populous city in Australia (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adelaide). A map showing the location of Adelaide can be found at https://www.google.com/maps/place/Adelaide+SA,+Australia. Flinders Medical Centre, opened in 1976, is a major public tertiary teaching hospital, co-located with Flinders University and the 130-bed Flinders Private Hospital in Bedford Park, a southern suburb of Adelaide (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flinders_Medical_Centre).

_Serratia marcescens__ is a Gram-negative bacillus and a member of the Enterobacteriaceae family. Although not normally part of the human flora, it is an important pathogen, especially in healthcare settings in adult and pediatric patients (1-8). Colonized or infected patients and contaminated environmental surfaces represent important reservoirs for _Serratia_. Transmission through carriage on the hands of healthcare personnel and on sinks and other hospital equipment are important routes in many nosocomial outbreaks.

_S. marcescens_ has also caused NICU (neonatal intensive care unit) outbreaks due to contamination of intravenous (IV) fluids (see ProMED-mail post Serratia marcescens - Venezuela (02): (CA) NICU, fatal 20120417.1103584). Contaminated liquid soap used for handwashing has also been found to be a source in another NICU outbreak (7). A multistate outbreak of _S. marcescens_ bloodstream infection was reported in 2009 to be associated with contamination of unopened prefilled heparin and saline syringes manufactured by single company, which grew _S. marcescens_ that genetically matched clinical isolates (8).

Genotyping of the isolates has been used to establish transmission pathways. A common source would be suggested if the genotypes of clinical isolates match each other, and the basin would be the possible, although perhaps incidental, "source" if the basin isolate's genotype matches that of the clinical isolates. How the basin was contaminated will need to be further investigated. - Mod.ML

